==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rodentia
<hw>Ro*den"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Rodent</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order
of mammals having two (rarely four) large incisor teeth in each jaw,
distant from the molar teeth. The rats, squirrels, rabbits, marmots, and
beavers belong to this order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The incisor teeth are long, curved, and strongly
enameled on the outside, so as to keep a cutting edge. They have a
persistent pulp and grow continuously.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rodeo</ent>⟦br⟧
